A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Montgomery County – Board of Education – Student Cellular Phone Policy
3 MC 13–25
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Montgomery County Board of Education to establish a
5 policy limiting the use of a cellular phone by a student during instructional time
6 except under certain circumstances; and generally relating to the Montgomery
7 County Board of Education and student cellular phone policy.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Education
10 Section 4–147
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 4–147.
17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “INSTRUCTIONAL TIME” MEANS ANY TIME DURING
18 THE SCHOOL DAY, EXCEPT A STUDENT’S LUNCH PERIOD.
19 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY IN MONTGOMERY COUNTY.
20 (C) THE MONTGOMERY COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL DEVELOP
21 AND IMPLEMENT A POLICY TO LIMIT THE USE OF CELLULAR PHONES BY STUDENTS
22 DURING INSTRUCTIONAL TIME.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1179*

2 HOUSE BILL 1179
1 (D) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION, THE
2 POLICY DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL:
3 (1) PROHIBIT A STUDENT FROM USING A CELLULAR PHONE DURING
4 INSTRUCTIONAL TIME; AND
5 (2) REQUIRE A STUDENT TO STORE THE STUDENT’S CELLULAR
6 PHONE IN A SECURE PLACE DURING INSTRUCTIONAL TIME, INCLUDING:
7 (I) A LOCKER;
8 (II) A CLOSED BACKPACK; OR
9 (III) A STORAGE DEVICE.
10 (E) THE POLICY DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SECTION MAY NOT PROHIBIT A
11 STUDENT FROM USING A CELLULAR PHONE:
12 (1) FOR ANY PURPOSE DOCUMENTED IN THE STUDENT’S
13 INDIVIDUALIZED EDUCATION PROGRAM;
14 (2) TO MONITOR OR ADDRESS A HEALTH ISSUE; OR
15 (3) WHEN DIRECTED BY AN EDUCATOR OR ADMINISTRATOR FOR
16 EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES.
17 (F) THE POLICY DEVELOPED UNDER THIS SECTION SHALL INCLUDE
18 APPROPRIATE DISCIPLINARY MEASURES FOR VIOLATIONS OF THE POLICY.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
20 1, 2025.

